# Technical References and Specifications

## FHIR Implementation Guidelines
When implementing FHIR features, always reference the official FHIR specification:
- Use proper FHIR resource names and operations
- Reference the [FHIR HTTP API specification](mdc:https:/www.hl7.org/fhir/http.html) for REST operations
- Include links to relevant FHIR specification sections
- Use `code` highlighting for FHIR operations like `$validate`, `$search`, etc.

## PostgreSQL Integration
When mentioning PostgreSQL features:
- Reference the [PostgreSQL documentation](mdc:https:/www.postgresql.org/docs/current) for database features
- Use proper PostgreSQL terminology and syntax
- Include links to relevant PostgreSQL documentation sections
- Follow PostgreSQL documentation style for database-related content

## Code Highlighting Standards
Use `code` highlighting for:
- Technical terms and operations
- File names and paths
- API endpoints and methods
- Configuration parameters
- Environment variables
- Database queries and operations

## External References
Always include proper references to:
- FHIR specification for FHIR implementations
- PostgreSQL documentation for database features
- Related internal documentation using relative markdown links
- External APIs and services when mentioned

